\begin_layout Subsubsection
Project Effort and Duration
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We can now compute the final estimation for the project effort and the project
 duration.
 As already mentioned, all the formulae are taken from the COCOMO manual
 (see references, section 1.4).
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The project effort (PM) is given by:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $PM=A*KSLOC^{E}*\prod EM(i)$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

where:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A=2.94 is a constant;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
KSLOC has been computed in section 2.1.7;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
EM(i) is the i-th Effort Multiplier, and the product ranges over all Cost
 Drivers;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The parameter E is given by:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $E=B+0.01*\sum SF(i)$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

where:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
B=0.91 is a constant;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
SF(i) is the i-th Scale Factor, and the sum ranges over all Scale Drivers;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Considering we have already computed:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\sum SF(i)=6.96$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\prod EM(i)=0.98861$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

we can substitute the values and we get:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $E=0.9796$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $PM=18.9$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Thus we have a project effort of 18.9 Person/Month.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

We can estimate the project duration as:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $TDEV=C*PM^{F}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

where C=3.67 is a constant.
 The parameter F is given by:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $F=D+0.2*(E-B)$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

where D=0.28 is a constant.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

By substituting the values we get:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $F=0.29392$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $TDEV=8.7$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Thus the project will take about 9 months.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

We can easily compute the number of persons involved as:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $NP=PM/TDEV=2.17$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

which is really close to the actual number of people in the team (2).
\end_layout

